00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,059
and I'm thankful that God has revealed himself to us

2
00:00:04,059 --> 00:00:05,820
through the pages of scripture.

3
00:00:05,820 --> 00:00:08,460
We think about that song, God's Word Changes Lives,

4
00:00:08,460 --> 00:00:10,500
and we think about the opportunity

5
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:12,180
that we have to read the Bible

6
00:00:12,180 --> 00:00:15,479
and how God has revealed himself to us

7
00:00:15,479 --> 00:00:17,100
through the pages of scripture.

8
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,780
I've often said this over the years

9
00:00:18,780 --> 00:00:21,239
and I believe it to be absolutely true,

10
00:00:21,239 --> 00:00:23,340
the heavens declare the glory of God,

11
00:00:23,340 --> 00:00:26,120
the firmament showeth forth his handiwork,

12
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:29,579
but the reality is that though the heavens declare

13
00:00:29,579 --> 00:00:32,540
that there is a God, the glory of God,

14
00:00:32,540 --> 00:00:35,459
the creation cries out that there's a creator,

15
00:00:35,459 --> 00:00:38,020
but it's through the written Word of God

16
00:00:38,020 --> 00:00:41,979
that he has revealed to us his attributes, his character.

17
00:00:41,979 --> 00:00:46,360
The fact that what we know about God is found in this book.

18
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:48,740
How do you know that God loves you?

19
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:51,180
Because he told us in his Word, amen?

20
00:00:51,180 --> 00:00:53,259
How do you know that he's coming again?

21
00:00:53,259 --> 00:00:56,740
We sang, coming again, coming again, how do we know?

22
00:00:56,779 --> 00:00:58,659
Because his Word tells us.

23
00:00:58,659 --> 00:01:00,860
And what a joy, we could go on and on

24
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:02,259
with all the attributes of God,

25
00:01:02,259 --> 00:01:03,779
but the preacher of yesteryear said this,

26
00:01:03,779 --> 00:01:06,239
to know God is to know his Word.

27
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:08,379
To know God is to know his Word.

28
00:01:08,379 --> 00:01:11,000
And I'm so thankful that as we read the scriptures,

29
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,500
he's given us his attributes,

30
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,940
and then we understand that he's taught us

31
00:01:14,940 --> 00:01:17,139
of the blessedness of redemption.

32
00:01:17,139 --> 00:01:19,040
Isn't it good to be saved?

33
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:22,980
I mean, honestly, what a joy to know Christ as your Savior.

34
00:01:22,980 --> 00:01:24,819
He is the Savior of the world,

35
00:01:24,819 --> 00:01:28,099
but when you know him as your Savior personally,

36
00:01:28,099 --> 00:01:30,819
we mention often, as you think about that great truth

37
00:01:30,819 --> 00:01:35,580
in Psalm 23, the Lord is my shepherd.

38
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:37,019
He is the great shepherd.

39
00:01:37,019 --> 00:01:39,059
He is the chief shepherd, the good shepherd,

40
00:01:39,059 --> 00:01:42,660
but he is my shepherd, and what a joy to know

41
00:01:42,660 --> 00:01:45,339
the blessedness of redemption, of salvation

42
00:01:45,339 --> 00:01:46,779
through the Lord Jesus Christ.

43
00:01:46,779 --> 00:01:48,620
I find that as we read the Bible,

44
00:01:48,620 --> 00:01:51,019
that not only does God reveal who he is,

45
00:01:51,019 --> 00:01:53,739
not only does he reveal the plan of redemption,

46
00:01:53,739 --> 00:01:55,819
but I believe that as you study the scriptures,

47
00:01:55,819 --> 00:01:57,980
you will find, you will notice,

48
00:01:57,980 --> 00:02:01,180
that God has graciously blessed us

49
00:02:01,180 --> 00:02:04,459
with instruction for godly living.

50
00:02:04,459 --> 00:02:09,179
As you read the Bible, it's abundantly clear and obvious

51
00:02:09,179 --> 00:02:12,119
that God is concerned with how we live our lives.

52
00:02:12,119 --> 00:02:16,660
Our conduct, our behavior is important to God.

53
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:19,139
The reality is that I would argue

54
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:21,619
that these portions of scripture

55
00:02:21,619 --> 00:02:24,539
that teach us of godly living

56
00:02:24,539 --> 00:02:28,699
are just as important as those portions of scripture

57
00:02:28,699 --> 00:02:31,860
that reveal to us the attributes of our God.

58
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:32,779
Amen?

59
00:02:32,779 --> 00:02:34,779
They're equally important.

60
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:36,100
They're a blessing.

61
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:37,740
I shared with somebody on Wednesday evening

62
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:39,899
in the foyer there at the end of the service,

63
00:02:39,899 --> 00:02:41,619
they were asking a question, and I said,

64
00:02:41,619 --> 00:02:45,460
I'm just so thankful that God has given us instruction

65
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:47,500
for godly living in his word,

66
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,779
and wouldn't it be a sad thing

67
00:02:48,779 --> 00:02:50,820
if you were being disobedient to God,

68
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:53,179
you didn't even know you were being disobedient to God

69
00:02:53,179 --> 00:02:55,179
because he didn't tell you in his word

70
00:02:55,179 --> 00:02:56,940
what he expected of you,

71
00:02:56,940 --> 00:02:58,779
and then you were held accountable for it.

72
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:00,199
That'd be unfortunate.

73
00:03:00,199 --> 00:03:04,300
But God has been gracious to give us instruction

74
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:05,440
for godly living.

75
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:08,059
He's told us some things that don't please him.

76
00:03:08,059 --> 00:03:10,300
He's told us some things that please him,

77
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,539
and that is wonderful.

78
00:03:11,539 --> 00:03:13,860
Listen, all scripture, the Bible says,

79
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:17,300
all scripture is given by inspiration of God.

80
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,899
That's John 3, 16,

81
00:03:18,899 --> 00:03:21,139
as much as it is any other verse of scripture,

82
00:03:21,139 --> 00:03:25,220
because all scripture is given by inspiration of God.

83
00:03:25,220 --> 00:03:28,380
It is not valid that we would take

84
00:03:28,380 --> 00:03:31,460
certain portions of the word of God and say,

85
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,960
well, I'm gonna accept this,

86
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,460
and I'm gonna cherish these verses,

87
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:36,559
but these ones over here,

88
00:03:36,559 --> 00:03:38,300
well, I'm gonna just discard those.

89
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:40,000
I'm not interested in those.

90
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,300
We're missing out because God's given us all of it,

91
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,860
and the Bible says that not only has it been given by God,

92
00:03:45,860 --> 00:03:47,899
but it's profitable.

93
00:03:47,899 --> 00:03:49,699
It's profitable for doctrine,

94
00:03:49,699 --> 00:03:53,500
for what we believe, for reproof, for correction.

95
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,339
Listen, there are times in which the word of God

96
00:03:55,339 --> 00:03:56,300
has to correct us.

97
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:59,440
It has to reprove us, and we ought to be thankful for that.

98
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:02,000
When the word of God steps on our toes, amen,

99
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:06,259
and it is God's word that reproves, and it corrects,

100
00:04:06,259 --> 00:04:09,759
and it says for instruction in righteousness,

101
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:11,899
that the man of God may be perfect,

102
00:04:11,899 --> 00:04:14,660
throughly furnished unto all good works.

103
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:17,820
And I'm thankful for all portions of God's word,

104
00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:20,980
the preacher said this with regard to those that would say,

105
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:23,420
well, I'm not sure about that verse.

106
00:04:23,420 --> 00:04:25,380
I don't really think that's what that means,

107
00:04:25,380 --> 00:04:27,660
or I really don't think we have to abide by that

108
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:28,779
or follow that.

109
00:04:28,779 --> 00:04:31,059
He would take out a marker or a pen knife and say,

110
00:04:31,059 --> 00:04:33,119
okay, take this and blot it out in your Bible,

111
00:04:33,119 --> 00:04:34,619
or cut it out of your Bible.

112
00:04:35,619 --> 00:04:38,119
And they would say, I'm not gonna do that.

113
00:04:38,119 --> 00:04:40,679
Well, you might as well, right?

114
00:04:40,679 --> 00:04:42,579
But we'd never wanna cut up our Bibles

115
00:04:42,579 --> 00:04:44,420
or mark out our Bibles,

116
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:46,559
but if we're not gonna live by it,

117
00:04:46,559 --> 00:04:48,459
if we're not gonna take the instruction,

118
00:04:48,459 --> 00:04:50,000
we might as well just do that,

119
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,119
because really that's what we're doing anyway.

120
00:04:52,119 --> 00:04:53,660
And so as we think about the word of God,

121
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:55,640
as we look at this portion of scripture,

122
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:58,959
I've titled the message, Walk in Wisdom.

123
00:04:58,959 --> 00:05:01,559
As we examine these couple of verses of scripture,

124
00:05:01,559 --> 00:05:03,660
I want you to, if you're taking notes,

125
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:07,160
number one, consider the importance of your testimony.

126
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:09,440
Notice Colossians four and verse number five.

127
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:12,359
The Bible says, walk in wisdom

128
00:05:12,359 --> 00:05:14,399
toward them that are without.

129
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:17,720
Walk in wisdom toward them that are without.

130
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:22,679
Redeeming the time, let your speech be always with grace,

131
00:05:22,679 --> 00:05:25,679
seasoned with salt, that you may know

132
00:05:25,679 --> 00:05:28,380
how you ought to answer every man.

133
00:05:28,380 --> 00:05:32,239
Number one, consider the importance of your testimony.

134
00:05:32,239 --> 00:05:34,660
We find here that the scripture starts

135
00:05:34,660 --> 00:05:36,619
with these three words, walk in wisdom,

136
00:05:36,619 --> 00:05:39,239
literally to behave ourselves wisely.

137
00:05:39,239 --> 00:05:41,880
We understand that Jesus said this in Matthew 10

138
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:45,440
and verse number 16, be you therefore wise as serpents

139
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,640
and harmless as doves.

140
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:51,279
We are to walk in wisdom, and we find that it's important,

141
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:53,420
it's imperative that we understand

142
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:55,559
that we're to behave ourselves wisely,

143
00:05:55,559 --> 00:05:57,600
that as we conduct ourselves,

144
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,040
when we think about our behavior,

145
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:01,559
that it would be that which is wise,

146
00:06:01,559 --> 00:06:02,760
that which is appropriate.

147
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:05,000
We find that if we lack wisdom,

148
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,880
God tells us that he has all wisdom,

149
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,440
and he says that if we but ask for wisdom,

150
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,160
that he would give it to us.

151
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,880
And what a blessing when we think about walking in wisdom

152
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,000
and behaving ourselves wisely.

153
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,000
I'm mindful as we think about this truth,

154
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,079
this instruction that is given to us

155
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:23,600
with the importance of our testimony,

156
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,920
I'm mindful of what the Bible says of David.

157
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:28,220
Hold your hand here and turn to the book of 1 Samuel,

158
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:32,059
if you will, and I want you to notice in chapter number 18,

159
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:35,019
we know that it was in chapter number 16 of 1 Samuel,

160
00:06:35,019 --> 00:06:38,899
where God had anointed through Samuel,

161
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:40,859
David to be the next king of Israel.

162
00:06:40,859 --> 00:06:43,820
He had a rejected Saul because of his disobedience,

163
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:46,579
and David had been anointed in chapter number 16.

164
00:06:46,579 --> 00:06:48,959
It's in chapter number 17 of the book of 1 Samuel

165
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:52,339
that God provides us with the record of David and Goliath.

166
00:06:52,339 --> 00:06:54,899
And then we come to the 18th chapter

167
00:06:54,899 --> 00:06:56,579
of the book of 1 Samuel,

168
00:06:56,579 --> 00:07:00,579
we begin to read some things about the behavior of David

169
00:07:00,579 --> 00:07:03,220
that I wanna highlight to you here this morning,

170
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:04,940
when we think about this truth,

171
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:08,079
walk in wisdom to behave ourselves wisely.

172
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:11,679
In 1 Samuel 18, notice in verse number five,

173
00:07:11,679 --> 00:07:12,519
the Bible says,

174
00:07:12,519 --> 00:07:17,160
and David went out whithersoever Saul sent him

175
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:21,000
and behaved himself wisely.

176
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,959
And Saul set him over the men of war

177
00:07:22,959 --> 00:07:25,359
and he was accepted in the sight of all the people

178
00:07:25,359 --> 00:07:27,720
and also in the sight of Saul's servants.

179
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,559
Skip down to verse number 14.

180
00:07:29,559 --> 00:07:30,959
Notice again, the Bible says,

181
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:35,959
and David behaved himself wisely in all his ways

182
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:39,260
and the Lord was with him.

183
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,899
It's interesting to me that the verse of Scripture

184
00:07:41,899 --> 00:07:45,079
ends with the statement that the Lord was with him.

185
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:47,679
And we find that this is revealed to us

186
00:07:47,679 --> 00:07:50,260
in a number of people's lives in the Old Testament,

187
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:53,200
how God is with them and causes them to prosper

188
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,399
and so on and so forth.

189
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:56,720
But we find that David's behavior

190
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:59,959
and that he behaved himself wisely in all his ways

191
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:02,760
is a key factor that helps us understand

192
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,519
why God was with him.

193
00:08:04,519 --> 00:08:05,480
Amen?

194
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,920
We understand as New Testament believers

195
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,399
that we are indwelled by the Spirit of God.

196
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:13,100
And what a blessing to understand the indwelling

197
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,200
of the Holy Spirit.

198
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,359
It is the earnest of our salvation.

199
00:08:16,359 --> 00:08:19,279
And we find that we are sealed under the day of redemption.

200
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:21,640
And what a joy and what a blessing that is.

201
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:24,799
He says, I will never leave thee nor forsake thee.

202
00:08:24,799 --> 00:08:27,200
But you understand as New Testament believers

203
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:31,040
that we can quench and grieve the Holy Spirit of God.

204
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,919
We can behave ourselves in manners

205
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,919
in which are not pleasing to God.

206
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:37,760
And we find that in those times of quenching

207
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,619
and grieving the Spirit of God,

208
00:08:39,619 --> 00:08:42,080
it's not that he departs from us,

209
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:45,479
but it is not as obvious that he is with us.

210
00:08:45,479 --> 00:08:47,119
Does that make sense to you this morning?

211
00:08:47,119 --> 00:08:48,900
And we find here that the Bible says

212
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:53,900
that David behaved himself wisely in all his ways

213
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,200
and the Lord was with him.

214
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,119
Notice how the passage of Scripture ends

215
00:08:58,119 --> 00:09:00,960
in 1 Samuel 18 and verse number 30.

216
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:03,880
Then the princes of the Philistines went forth

217
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,359
and it came to pass after they went forth

218
00:09:06,359 --> 00:09:11,039
that David behaved himself more wisely

219
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:13,400
than all the servants of Saul

