00:09:50,919 --> 00:09:52,919
to these believers in Colossae?

234
00:09:52,919 --> 00:09:55,280
He's saying this, he's saying walk in wisdom

235
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:58,960
toward the unbelievers, toward them that are without.

236
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,359
That when we would understand

237
00:10:00,359 --> 00:10:02,819
understand our conduct and our behavior,

238
00:10:02,819 --> 00:10:04,159
that we would understand,

239
00:10:04,159 --> 00:10:05,879
as someone of yesteryear said,

240
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:07,919
that sometimes your life might be

241
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:10,059
the only Bible that some lost person

242
00:10:10,059 --> 00:10:11,919
ever reads or ever observes,

243
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:14,079
and the reality is that there are people

244
00:10:14,079 --> 00:10:15,619
that are watching us.

245
00:10:15,619 --> 00:10:17,619
We don't even know who those people are.

246
00:10:17,619 --> 00:10:18,979
Who is observing you?

247
00:10:18,979 --> 00:10:20,279
And let me ask this,

248
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:23,199
what is it that they're observing?

249
00:10:23,199 --> 00:10:25,439
Are we walking in wisdom toward them

250
00:10:25,439 --> 00:10:27,119
that are without understanding

251
00:10:27,119 --> 00:10:29,879
that there are people that we come in contact with

252
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:32,139
that God has given us the opportunity

253
00:10:32,139 --> 00:10:34,079
to show the Lord Jesus Christ,

254
00:10:34,079 --> 00:10:36,319
and in our lives that he, Jesus,

255
00:10:36,319 --> 00:10:37,979
would be exalted and magnified,

256
00:10:37,979 --> 00:10:39,919
that we'd say, as John the Baptist said,

257
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:42,219
he must increase and I must decrease,

258
00:10:42,219 --> 00:10:43,839
that as our lives,

